# Rocky × Horizon — Forked Theme Development Standards

This is a **managed fork** of Shopify's Horizon theme. Upstream Horizon receives ongoing updates. Every decision made here must balance Rocky customization with the ability to pull those updates cleanly.

---

## 1. The Core Rule: Net-New Files First

Before touching any file that exists in the upstream Horizon codebase, ask: _can this be accomplished in a new file instead?_

| Situation | Correct approach |
|---|---|
| New page section | Create `sections/r-*.liquid` |
| New reusable UI block | Create `blocks/r-*.liquid` |
| New shared snippet | Create `snippets/r-*.liquid` |
| New JS behaviour | Create `assets/r-*.js` |
| CSS shared across Rocky sections/blocks | Add to `assets/r-base.css` |
| Extending an upstream section | ⚠️ Prefer `sections/r-*` using `{% content_for 'blocks' %}` instead |
| New page-type layout | Create an alternate template e.g. `templates/product.r-pdp.json` |
| Fixing a bug in an upstream file | Acceptable — register in `.gitattributes` as `merge=ours` before editing |
| Adjusting design tokens / colour | Edit `snippets/theme-styles-variables.liquid` (already `merge=ours`) |

**Upstream files** are any that do _not_ begin with `r-` in `sections/`, `snippets/`, `blocks/`, or `assets/`.

---

## 2. Naming Convention — `r-` Prefix on Everything Rocky Owns

All net-new files **must** use the `r-` prefix. This is the primary merge-safety mechanism: it guarantees zero naming collisions with upstream Horizon files now and in future releases.

**Files:**

```
sections/r-journal-index.liquid       ✅
sections/r-hero-campaign.liquid       ✅
sections/hero.liquid                  ❌ upstream — do not create a duplicate

blocks/r-shoppable-card.liquid        ✅
blocks/text.liquid                    ❌ upstream — do not create a duplicate

snippets/r-rewards-bar.liquid         ✅
snippets/price.liquid                 ❌ upstream — do not duplicate

assets/r-base.css                     ✅
assets/r-store-locator.js             ✅
assets/base.css                       ❌ upstream — do not edit

templates/product.r-pdp.json          ✅  (alternate template)
templates/product.json                ⚠️  upstream — prefer alternate instead
```

**CSS class names** (BEM, `r-` prefixed):

```css
/* ✅ */
.r-journal-card { }
.r-journal-card__image { }
.r-journal-card--featured { }

/* ❌ could collide with upstream or future Horizon components */
.journal-card { }
.card { }
```

**CSS custom properties** (scoped to element, `--r-` prefixed):

```css
/* ✅ */
.r-journal-card {
  --r-journal-card-gap: 1.5rem;
  gap: var(--r-journal-card-gap);
}

/* ❌ generic names bleed into upstream token space */
.r-journal-card {
  --gap: 1.5rem;
}
```

**Web component / custom element names** (`r-` prefixed):

```js
customElements.define('r-rewards-bar', RewardsBar);
customElements.define('r-store-locator', StoreLocator);
```

```html
<r-rewards-bar data-threshold="{{ settings.free_shipping_threshold }}">
```

---

## 3. CSS Architecture

### 3.1 `assets/r-base.css` — Rocky Shared Stylesheet

One file for CSS shared across **two or more** Rocky sections, blocks, or snippets. It is loaded identically to `base.css` — preloaded and render-blocking — via `snippets/stylesheets.liquid`:

```liquid
{{ 'overflow-list.css' | asset_url | preload_tag: as: 'style' }}
{{ 'base.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag: preload: true }}
{{ 'r-base.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag: preload: true }}
```

`snippets/stylesheets.liquid` is registered in `.gitattributes` as `merge=ours`.

**Belongs in `r-base.css`:**
- Rocky design tokens (brand colours, editorial type scale) that extend but never overwrite upstream tokens
- Utility classes used across multiple Rocky files (`.r-page-width`, `.r-sr-only`)
- Component CSS consumed by 2+ Rocky files (e.g. a rewards progress bar used in both cart drawer and mini-cart)
- Upstream overrides that must apply globally — with a comment explaining why

**Does NOT belong in `r-base.css`:**
- CSS for a single section or block — that goes in the file's own `{% stylesheet %}` tag
- Arbitrary upstream class overrides without a documented reason

### 3.2 Sections and Blocks Are CSS Self-Contained

Every `sections/r-*.liquid` and `blocks/r-*.liquid` carries **all of its own CSS** inside `{% stylesheet %}`. Do not reach into `r-base.css` for section-specific rules.

```liquid
{%- comment -%} sections/r-journal-index.liquid {%- endcomment -%}

<section class="r-journal-index" ...>
  ...
</section>

{% stylesheet %}
  .r-journal-index {
    --r-journal-index-gap: 2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--r-journal-index-gap);
  }

  .r-journal-index__card { }
  .r-journal-index__card--featured { }

  @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
    .r-journal-index {
      --r-journal-index-gap: 3rem;
    }
  }
{% endstylesheet %}
```

### 3.3 Never Edit `assets/base.css`

`base.css` is upstream. Override globally in `r-base.css` with an explanatory comment:

```css
/* Override: upstream .page-width is 1400px — Rocky brand standard is 1360px */
.page-width {
  max-width: 136rem;
}
```

