## 15. Quick-Reference: What Not to Do

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do instead |
|---|---|
| Edit `assets/base.css` | Override globally in `assets/r-base.css` |
| Create files without `r-` prefix | Always prefix Rocky-owned files |
| Duplicate an upstream section file | Create `sections/r-*` and compose with blocks |
| Edit upstream templates directly | Create `templates/product.r-*.json` alternates |
| Use upstream CSS class names as BEM roots | Prefix all Rocky BEM roots with `r-` |
| Use `--` or generic CSS variable names | Prefix Rocky variables with `--r-` |
| Add Rocky copy to upstream locale namespaces | Add under `rocky.*` in locale files |
| Add metafields to any namespace but `rocky` | Use `rocky` metafield namespace in admin |
| Write Rocky JS inside upstream `.js` assets | Use `assets/r-*.js` |
| Define custom elements without `r-` prefix | Use `customElements.define('r-*', ...)` |
| Embed app scripts in upstream files | Use app blocks in Rocky sections |
| Modify `sections/header-group.json` | Compose through sections or create `r-*-group.json` |
| Use `{# Rocky: #}` in Liquid | Use valid `{%- # r: description -%}` syntax |
| Skip `.gitattributes` when editing upstream | Always register the file before editing |
| Push changes directly to the live theme | Use dev/preview themes; gate production pushes |
| Hardcode hex values in CSS | Always use `var(--color-*)` or `var(--r-*)` tokens |
| Define `--color-*` variables in Rocky files | Those are upstream-owned; use `--r-*` prefix |
| Add extra scheme tokens to `:root` | Scope them to `.color-scheme-*` in `r-base.css` |
| Create new scheme IDs (scheme-4+) | Repurpose scheme-1/2/3 with Rocky palette |
| Add scheme settings to `settings_schema.json` | Rocky extra tokens go in `r-base.css` |
